      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "XTRASCENT (2) didn't go a yard on the Heavy deck two back before a better effort last start when beaten 1.3L at Moruya. His first-up effort at this track and trip was superb and that rating stands out in this field. A return to that level will see him hard to hold out. KIP STAR (5) finished off well on debut when coming from the back of the pack, ending up 1.6L off the winner. He'll be better for the debut effort and he makes plenty of appeal with natural improvement on the cards. JENNI MOO MOO (4) comes across from the Ciaron Maher stable and has her first run for the local stable. Drawn the inside though and it wouldn't surprise to see her fire. JUSTWATCHHER (9) looks well placed in this company and she won't be far away fresh.",
